<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2797] Release artifact expects a git repository for the release audit tool (RAT)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2797</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running gradle on the RC0 for 0.9, we get an error because the build expects to find a git repo here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;	line 68 of build.gradle: def repo = Grgit.open(project.file(&apos;.&apos;))
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and we get this error message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;	FAILURE: Build failed with an exception.

	* Where:
	Build file &apos;kafka-0.9.0.0-src/build.gradle&apos; line: 68

	* What went wrong:
	A problem occurred evaluating root project &apos;kafka-0.9.0.0-src&apos;.
	&amp;gt; repository not found: kafka-0.9.0.0-src

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The definitions for rat make sense when working on a git branch, but not for the release artifact. One way around this is to disable rat by commenting out the corresponding lines, but that isn&apos;t what the README file says.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
